<article>
  <section>
    <p>Our family started AnnaLeah and Mary for Truck Safety, a 501(c)3 non-profit organization, for raising funds for truck safety research. We are starting with underride guards because if the truck in front of us had a guard that prevented our car from going under it, AnnaLeah and Mary would be here today.</p>
        <%= image_tag("/content/SAFER_Barrier_crash_photo.jpg", alt: "Photo of a racecar crashing against a Steel and Foam Energy Reduction barrier at high speed. While the car is damaged, the driver is visibly unharmed.") %>
    <p class="caption">&copy; Dean Sicking, SAFER barrier, used with permission </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Dean Sicking has saved lives through the SAFER barrier he designed for NASCAR. He is interested in taking this technology and using it in underride guards.</li>
      <li>Other engineers have contacted us over the last year looking to work on underride guards.</li>
      <li>We are working with universities and their engineering programs to get more engineers thinking and working toward real life solutions to this problem.</li>
    </ul>
